In most buildings, tenants receive a take-it-or-leave-it notice at a legall=
y mandated date before their lease is up informing them of their new rate. =
Flow's managers find that cold and impersonal. Its staffers want a more cus=
tomized approach, like inviting tenants to coffee months in advance to disc=
uss areas the building could improve on.

And (2) there is a lot of blather about being a tech company that doesn=E2=
=80=99t seem all that real, but that induces venture capitalists to write l=
arge checks:

Neumann started Flow in the summer of 2022 after landing a $350 million che=
ck from Andreessen Horowitz, better known as A16z, one of Silicon Valley's =
most prestigious venture firms. It was the single largest investment in the=
 firm's history, instantly making Flow worth a billion dollars on paper. ..=
.
A16z's funding announcement praised Neumann as a "visionary leader" and was=
 full of soaring rhetoric about solving America's housing crisis and removi=
ng the soullessness of apartments. Absent were specifics of how Flow would =
actually accomplish these lofty goals. =E2=80=A6
Based on the early accounts of Flow, you might have expected a radically ne=
w way of living. There was talk of crypto wallets and a rent-to-own model t=
hrough which residents could build equity.
Neither is happening anytime soon.

Love it! Arguably the basic business model=C2=A0of WeWork was that Adam Neu=
mann took  $14 billion of SoftBank Group Corp.=E2=80=99s money, gave $13 bi=
llion of it to companies to subsidize their office rent and happy hours, an=
d kept $1 billion of it for himself. Not bad! But if the basic business mod=
el of Flow is that Adam Neumann will take hundreds of millions of dollars o=
f Andreessen Horowitz=E2=80=99s money, give most of it to twentysomethings =
to subsidize their apartment rents and happy hours, and keep a few building=
s for himself, then how could anyone object to that? I just hope he=E2=80=
=99ll scale it up rapidly and go back to SoftBank for more money.=C2=A0

 =20
   =20
      Elsewhere in selling real estate visions to tech investors
   =20
 =20

Does Neumann overcomplicate things? Is it simpler to just go to tech invest=
ors and say =E2=80=9Chello, I am building a new city where everyone will be=
 either a tech founder or a model, and nobody will be ugly or poor, doesn=
=E2=80=99t that sound nice,=C2=A0give me some money=E2=80=9D? Here is a New=
 York Times  story about a guy named Dryden Brown, who has raised money fro=
m investors including Paradigm and Sam Altman for =E2=80=9Chis company, Pra=
xis, which has an ambitious goal: to create a new city on the Mediterranean=
,=E2=80=9D with stuff like this:

An internal Praxis branding guide =E2=80=A6=C2=A0denounces =E2=80=9Cenemies=
 of vitality,=E2=80=9D who =E2=80=9Creject what they consider the optional =
=E2=80=98European beauty standards.=E2=80=9D It goes on to extol =E2=80=9Ct=
raditional, European/Western beauty standards on which the civilized world,=
 at its best points, has always found success.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6
According to several former Praxis employees who spoke on the condition of =
anonymity because they signed nondisclosure agreements, Mr. Brown had discu=
ssed wanting to attract tech talent to his city by introducing founders to =
=E2=80=9Chot girls.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6
Internal Praxis documents outline three =E2=80=9Cpersona groups=E2=80=9D wh=
o will populate the Praxis city. They are =E2=80=9Cwarriors,=E2=80=9D who a=
re =E2=80=9Cmuscular=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cclean=E2=80=9D and protect socie=
ty from threats; =E2=80=9Cpriests,=E2=80=9D who are =E2=80=9Cvery thin,=E2=
=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cdefine the values and beliefs of society=E2=80=9D; and =
=E2=80=9Cmerchants,=E2=80=9D who are =E2=80=9Cportly=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9C=
bearded,=E2=80=9D and include venture capitalists and cryptocurrency profes=
sionals.

=E2=80=9CExposed to the classics by his tutor, Mr. Brown read Ayn Rand and =
the Austrian economists in high school=E2=80=9D is one of the nicer things =
that the article has to say about him. Martin Shkreli is apparently a membe=
r.

