  [3] That is, in 2024 Ohtani will earn $68 million payable in 2034, and th=
ey=E2=80=99ll have to fund that in 2026. (And in 2025, he=E2=80=99ll earn a=
nother $68 million payable in 2034, funded in 2027, etc.) The funding oblig=
ation is the present value of the deferred comp; the discount rate specifie=
d in the contract is 5% per year, though it can go up if rates are higher. =
So 68/(1.05)^8 =3D 46.=20


  [4] I have no idea what the actual enforcement mechanism is here, or if h=
e can get out if they don't fund it, or if he can sue to force them to fund=
 it, etc.


