<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A week before Credit Suisse Goup AG collapsed =
and was taken over by UBS Group AG, it was desperately trying to hold on to=
 its employees: It was trying to=C2=A0<em>avoid=C2=A0</em>collapse, and if =
the good employees all left it would definitely collapse, so it would do an=
ything to keep them. It collapsed anyway.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A=C2=A0week=C2=A0<em>after=C2=A0</em>Credit Su=
isse collapsed and was taken over by UBS, it was, uh, pretty keen to get ri=
d of all of the employees? Like UBS <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/33697175.257398/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlua=
W9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMjgvdWJzLWN1dHMtb3V0LWNyZWRpdC1zdWlzc2U_Y21waWQ9=
QkJEMTIxNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR=
0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMjE0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cB291a6acf" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">  pretty immediately signaled</a> =E2=80=9Cwe are=
 going to fire most of Credit Suisse,=E2=80=9D and then it <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33697175.257398/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm=
xvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMTkvY3JlZGl0LXN1aXNzZS1wcmVwY=
XJlcy1mb3ItbW9yZS1qb2ItY3V0cy1maW5hbmNpYWwtbmV3cy1zYXlzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEyMTQy=
M19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV9=
0ZXJtPTIzMTIxNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf6=
0730a1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">  set to work doing that</a>. Losing tons of Credit Suisse =
employees <em>now</em> wouldn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0sink the combined company, sin=
ce there are so many UBS people left. If anyone wants to leave voluntarily,=
 hey great that=E2=80=99s super, saves UBS some effort.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The problem is that the pre-collapse Credit Su=
isse gave employees gobs of money to keep them, and then it collapsed, and =
they left, and the post-collapse Credit Suisse <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33697175.257398/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLm=
NvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTItMTMvdWJzLXN0ZXBzLXVwLWJpZC10by1jbGF3LWJhY=
2stY2FzaC1mcm9tLWNyZWRpdC1zdWlzc2UtZGVmZWN0b3JzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEyMTQyM19NT05F=
WVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI=
zMTIxNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB49423787" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;">  would rather have the money back</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">UBS Group AG has stepped up an effort to recou=
p hundreds of millions in cash bonuses that Credit Suisse paid to retain de=
almakers before the lender=E2=80=99s collapse.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">UBS has contacted hundreds of bankers and offe=
red some multi-year payment plans amid efforts to claw back a chunk of the =
1.2 billion Swiss francs ($1.38 billion) in restricted cash bonuses, known =
internally as upfront cash awards, according to people familiar with the ma=
tter and documents seen by Bloomberg News. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The bank awarded cash bonuses with strings att=
ached to thousands of managing directors and directors in early 2022 as wel=
l as this year in an effort to cushion the blow of a bonus pool shrinking a=
mid the bank=E2=80=99s struggles. Then the bank saw a flood of departures.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Deferred awards are typically given in restric=
ted shares that the bank can just cancel. But to retain talent amid multipl=
e restructurings and a slumping stock price, Credit Suisse handed out cash =
with a clause requiring employees to repay some of the bonus if they left t=
he firm within three years.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If a bank says to an employee =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=
=80=99ll give you $1 million to stay, but we=E2=80=99ll pay it out in three=
 years,=E2=80=9D then the employee is taking the bank=E2=80=99s credit risk=
.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: tran=
sparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0If the bank says to an employee =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99ll give you $=
1 million to stay, and we=E2=80=99ll pay it out now, but if you leave withi=
n three years you have to pay us back,=E2=80=9D then the bank is taking the=
 employee=E2=80=99s credit risk. By the end, at Credit Suisse, its employee=
s were apparently a better bet than it was. But not a risk-free bet.</p>
