<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Arguably Adam Neumann has two valuable and lar=
gely unrelated=C2=A0skills:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">He=E2=80=99s a pretty good real estat=
e guy, in the sense that he is good at acquiring buildings, making them nic=
e places to live or work in, and finding tenants who will pay to rent them.=
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">He has some sort of Jedi-mind-tri=
ck power where he can walk into a room full of venture capitalists, tell th=
em about his real estate company, and have them say =E2=80=9Cyou are a tech=
 visionary, take all of our money.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Like there are plenty of cases of people who p=
itch=C2=A0<em>bad tech company ideas=C2=A0</em>to venture capitalists, and =
get funded, and blow up. But Neumann=E2=80=99s schtick seems to be that he =
pitches=C2=A0<em>good real estate companies=C2=A0</em>to venture capitalist=
s, and gets lavishly overfunded, and =E2=80=A6=C2=A0well, <a href=3D"https:=
